<subSubSection id="CDED6571A30D0A1E93760235C2790841" pageId="27" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="854836FAA30D0A1E93760235C2790841" blockId="27.[264,1323,1305,1611]" pageId="27" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B783EAE8A30D0A1E93760235C7390B38" box="[264,366,1305,1330]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="42">Remarks</emphasis>
. —This species has been reported only by 
<bibRefCitation id="E1664B0BA30D0A1E91FB0235C27D0B39" author="Cairns, S. D." box="[901,1066,1305,1331]" pageId="27" pageNumber="42" refId="ref14291" refString="Cairns, S. D. (1982) Antarctic and Subantarctic Scleractinia. Antarctic Research Series, 34 (1), 74 pp., 18 pls., 14 maps." type="book" year="1982">Cairns (1982)</bibRefCitation>
from the continental slope off 
<collectingCountry id="FDE0766AA30D0A1E9306026DC7F50B51" box="[376,418,1345,1371]" name="Iceland" pageId="27" pageNumber="42">Isla</collectingCountry>
Desolación (
<typeStatus id="5A4C8858A30D0A1E9040026DC4250B51" box="[574,626,1345,1371]" pageId="27" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
locality) and off Taltal, 
<collectingCountry id="FDE0766AA30D0A1E91ED026DC5850B51" box="[915,978,1345,1371]" name="Chile" pageId="27" pageNumber="42">Chile</collectingCountry>
(25°– 
<geoCoordinate id="E0C3503DA30D0A1E9661026DC20F0B51" box="[1055,1112,1345,1371]" degrees="53" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="27" pageNumber="42" precision="55555" value="-53.0">53°S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity id="420F9B1FA30D0A1E961B026DC2AB0B51" box="[1125,1276,1345,1371]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.423" metricValueMax="1.896" metricValueMin="0.95" pageId="27" pageNumber="42" unit="m" value="1423.0" valueMax="1896.0" valueMin="950.0">950–1896 m</quantity>
), as well as off 
<collectingCountry id="FDE0766AA30D0A1E93F00245C7930B89" box="[398,452,1385,1411]" name="Peru" pageId="27" pageNumber="42">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<geoCoordinate id="E0C3503DA30D0A1E93A80245C4570B89" box="[470,512,1385,1411]" degrees="8" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="27" pageNumber="42" precision="55555" value="-8.0">8°S</geoCoordinate>
) and the Falkland Plateau (as shallow as 
<quantity id="420F9B1FA30D0A1E91910245C2690B89" box="[1007,1086,1385,1411]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.95" pageId="27" pageNumber="42" unit="m" value="595.0">595 m</quantity>
). It is easily recognized by having a basal scar from which it asexually detaches from an attached anthocaulus. 
<bibRefCitation id="E1664B0BA30D0A1E932F0295C7A00BD9" author="Cairns, S. D." box="[337,503,1465,1491]" pageId="27" pageNumber="42" refId="ref14325" refString="Cairns, S. D. (1989) A revision of the ahermatypic Scleractinia of the Philippine Islands and adjacent waters. Part 1: Fungiacyathidae, Micrabaciidae, Turbinoliinae, and Flabellidae. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 486, 136 pp., 42 pls." type="book" year="1989">Cairns (1989</bibRefCitation>
: Table 6) implied that 
<taxonomicName id="42F74D79A30D0A1E91570295C5E60BD8" baseAuthorityName="Cairns" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[809,945,1465,1490]" class="Anthozoa" family="Flabellidae" genus="Truncatoflabellum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="27" pageNumber="42" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="truncum">
<emphasis id="B783EAE8A30D0A1E91570295C5E60BD8" box="[809,945,1465,1490]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="42">T. truncum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="42F74D79A30D0A1E976B0295C4120BF1" authority="Keller, 1981" authorityName="Keller" authorityYear="1981" class="Anthozoa" family="Flabellidae" genus="Truncatoflabellum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="27" pageNumber="42" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="trapezoideum">
<emphasis id="B783EAE8A30D0A1E976B0295C7F00BF0" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="42">T. trapezoideum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E1664B0BA30D0A1E93CE02CDC4120BF1" author="Keller, N. B." box="[432,581,1505,1531]" pageId="27" pageNumber="42" pagination="28 - 39" refId="ref15481" refString="Keller, N. B. (1981) The solitary madreporarian corals. In: Kuznetsov, A. P. &amp; Mironov, A. N. (Ed) Benthos of the Submarine Mountains Marcus-Necker and adjacent Pacific Regions, P. P. Shirshov Institute of Oceanology, Moscow, pp. 28 - 39, 2 pls." type="book chapter" year="1981">Keller, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the latter known only from the Marcus Necker Ridge at 
<quantity id="420F9B1FA30D0A1E968E02CDC7760829" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.63" pageId="27" pageNumber="42" unit="m" value="1630.0">1630 m</quantity>
, but 
<bibRefCitation id="E1664B0BA30D0A1E93240125C46B0829" author="Cairns, S. D. &amp; Hoeksema, B. W. &amp; van der Land, J." box="[346,572,1545,1571]" pageId="27" pageNumber="42" pagination="13 - 46" refId="ref14671" refString="Cairns, S. D., Hoeksema, B. W. &amp; van der Land, J. (1999) Appendix, List of extant stony corals. Atoll Research Bulletin 459, 13 - 46." type="journal article" year="1999">Cairns et al. (1999)</bibRefCitation>
listed them as separate species. Both species are poorly known and should be closely compared when more specimens are available.
</paragraph>
